attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64 (stripped to external PDB), for MS Windows

exiftool.ImageFileCharacteristics: No relocs, Executable, No line numbers, No symbols, Large address aware, No debug

threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factor was that it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a malicious loader designed to decrypt and execute shellcode while evading analysis. It exhibits several high-confidence indicators of malware: 1) Anti-analysis/sandbox detection in sub_401630, which uses PostThreadMessageA and PeekMessageA combined with a timing check (GetTickCount/Sleep) to detect if the execution environment is being accelerated. 2) Dynamic payload decryption and execution in sub_401595, where it allocates memory (VirtualAlloc), performs a XOR-based decryption loop, modifies memory protections to executable (VirtualProtect), and spawns a new thread (CreateThread) to run the payload. 3) Manual import resolution in sub_401563, which provides the decrypted shellcode with direct access to GetModuleHandleA and GetProcAddress. 4) Self-modification behaviors in sub_401c40, which iterates through sections and applies PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE permissions.
